# GameNative — Hardware Detection + Game Configuration System

## Why games are crashing on boot

Games crash before launching for several specific reasons that the current
app does not handle. Fix ALL of these before implementing the configuration UI:

### Crash cause 1 — Wrong Proton/Wine version for the game
Proton 10.0 is cutting-edge and some games are incompatible with it.
Elden Ring, GTA V, and many others work better on Proton 8.0 or 9.0.
The app must not hardcode Proton 10.0 for all games.

### Crash cause 2 — Missing WINEPREFIX initialization
If the Wine prefix does not exist or is corrupt, Wine crashes immediately
with no useful error. The app must verify the prefix exists and is valid
before launch, and re-create it if not.

### Crash cause 3 — Wrong DX version detection
The app may be forcing DX12 (VKD3D) on a DX9/DX11 game or vice versa.
VKD3D attempting to initialize on a DX9 game causes an immediate crash.

### Crash cause 4 — Turnip/Mesa version mismatch
If the community Turnip .so version does not match the Mesa version
in the container, Vulkan initialization fails silently and the game
crashes at the black screen.

### Crash cause 5 — vm.max_map_count not applied
If the sysctl failed silently (non-root device, wrong container scope),
games that need large map counts (Elden Ring needs 300k+) crash with
"mmap failed" or allocator errors.

### Crash cause 6 — Proton runtime path wrong
If Proton is installed to a path the app cannot find, WINE env var
points to nothing and the process exits immediately.

